==Talking to the Wise Old Man==
* '''Wise Old Man:''' Greetings, [player name].
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Queen Ellamaria has sent me to seek your guidance.}}
** '''Player:''' Queen Ellamaria has sent me to seek your guidance.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Ellamaria? Well, if you're in her service my guidance is this: do the fastest run that you can off the shortest pier you can find.
** '''Player:''' You know Queen Ellamaria?
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Oh yes, we go way back, long before she married that fool the King of Varrock. She wasn't always royal you know.
** '''Player:''' Really?
** '''Wise Old Man:''' No, in her youth she was a barmaid at the Blue Moon inn. All that fancy talk, that's just for show. No, the Ellamaria I knew was as common as muck, until she lucked onto good King Roald.
** '''Player:''' I'll certainly look at her in a different light when I return to Varrock.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' So what sort of guidance has Little-Miss-Hoity-Toity sent you to seek?
** '''Player:''' I am supposed to gain some knowledge of diplomacy and persuasion from you.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' That is an area that - luckily for you, young [player name] - I have studied. Have you heard of the diplomat known as Charos?
** '''Player:''' Charos? I must say the name rings a bell...
** '''Player:''' Charos...
** '''Player:''' Yes, I remember! Once, during my travels to Morytania, I came upon an item of magical jewellery called the Ring of Charos.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' You have found the Ring of Charos?!? Tell me - do you still have it in your possession?
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the Ring of Charos:}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes, I'm wearing it at the moment. Is it important, then?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the Ring of Charos is in the player’s inventory:}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes, I have it in my bag. Is it important, then?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the Ring of Charos is in the player’s bank, grave, in death’s office or any item retrieval service:}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes, I have it stored somewhere. Is it important, then?
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' Important?!? This ring possesses hidden power beyond belief! Go and get it, and I will tell you its secrets.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player is not wearing the ring or in their inventory:}}
*** '''Player:''' No, I'm afraid that I lost it at some point.
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' Lost the Ring of Charos?!? That is indeed a disastrous turn of events. This ring that you have so casually thrown away possesses hidden power beyond belief.
*** '''Player:''' How can I re-obtain the Ring of Charos?
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' If everything I have heard about Charos's ring is true, it will not stay lost forever. Where did you originally find it?
*** '''Player:''' I ... um ... 'borrowed' it from a rather shady character called Fenkenstrain.
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' In order to find the ring it may be wise to return to Fenkenstrain - he may have found a way to regain it. If you manage to reobtain the ring, return to me and I will reveal its secrets to you.
*** {{tact|end}}
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Charos rose to power under the rule of Lord Drakan of Morytania, his only living servant. The Vampyre Lord suffered the existence of Charos because of the talents that this sophisticated diplomat had to offer.
** '''Player:''' The art of persuasion?
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Indeed. Charos had many uses - spy, assassin, negotiator - because he could convince anyone to do his wishes. These talents were in some part Charos's own, but greatly enhanced by the ring that he fashioned.
** '''Player:''' The Ring of Charos.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Exactly. One who wears the ring must possess some innate ability of their own, which the ring enhances so that the wearer can convince all but the most strong- minded to do their bidding.
** '''Player:''' What happened to Charos? And why did Fenkenstrain have the ring?
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Charos had a castle built on the northern coast of Morytania, where he dwelt for many years in service to Drakan. None really know what became of him, but some say that he became too certain of his abilities,
** '''Wise Old Man:''' and turned them on his master. This would have been his ultimate downfall, for the ring's power would have had little or no effect upon Drakan.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Fenkenstrain probably found the ring many years later, buried somewhere within the depths of Charos's castle.
** '''Player:''' So what you are telling me is that nobody really knows what happened to Charos? That he could still be alive? And if he is still alive...
** '''Wise Old Man:''' ...he would naturally come looking for the ring that is his by right. But I don't believe that you should worry about that - it has been many years since his disappearance, and the likelyhood is that he is dead.
** '''Player:''' Still - it doesn't inspire me with much confidence.
** '''Wise Old Man:''' I could activate the power within this ring for you, but for me to do that I must know that you will use it wisely. To do that I must ask you a few questions, to see how good a diplomat you can be.
** '''Player:''' Okay, go ahead...
** {{tact|Note that the answers are randomly shuffled; Answer A may switch to C/B if retaking the test.}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|1/7: Two goblins are fighting over the colour of their armour. What do you do?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} Kill them both and steal their bronze spears.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} Leave them to it. Armour's not going to help - any noob could take them.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} Show them a range of colours so that they can come to a compromise.}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|2/7: A Drunken dwarf offers you a kebab. What do you do?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} Take his generous gift even though you have no need for it.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} Run away leaving the lonely dwarf on his own.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} Stand there until he gets annoyed and attacks you.}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|3/7: Are you enjoying your experience of Farming?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} Definitely.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} Yes.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} It's absolutely, unquestionably the most interesting thing I've ever done!}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|4/7: A dwarf asks you to put on a silly golden helmet so that you can be fired from a cannon into a wall. What do you do?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} Refuse this crazy request blankly.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} Put on the silly helmet and jump into the cannon.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} Put the helmet on the dwarf and fire him into the wall.}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|5/7: You meet Pkmaster0036 in the wilderness who asks you who is the greatest player killer in the world. How do you answer?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} Cower in fear and quickly cast teleport to Varrock.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} You of course Pkmaster0036, no one could ever challenge your greatness!<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} I am, prepare to meet your doom Pkmaster0036!}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|6/7: Queen Ellamaria orders you to go on a foolish quest without any offer of reward. What do you say?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} I'll do whatever you ask - I just love the monarchy!<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} Ask me nicely and I might consider it.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} Stop ordering me about and get behind the bar where you belong!}}
** {{tbox|{{colour|#7f0000|7/7: A Draynor bank guard asks you if you've seen any suspicious characters lately, because the bank has been robbed. What do you say?}}<br />{{colour|#000080|[A]}} No, especially not that wise old man, who doesn't look at all suspicious.<br />{{colour|#000080|[B]}} If I do I'll let you know.<br />{{colour|#000080|[C]}} Yes, that wise old man over there looks incredibly dodgy.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay, I've answered your questions - what's the verdict?
** '''Wise Old Man:''' Mmmm, it was close but..
** {{tcond|If the player failed the diplomacy test:}}
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' ... but I'm afraid that you don't seem to have the aptitude. To you, the Ring of Charos is but a worthless trinket.
*** {{tselect|Select an option}}
*** {{topt|I can't believe that - can I have another go?}}
**** '''Player:''' I can't believe that - can I have another go?
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' Well, if you think it will do any good ... here goes then-
**** {{tact|above}}
*** {{topt|Oh well, that's that I suppose.}}
**** '''Player:''' Oh well, that's that I suppose.
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' Now look, don't start making me feel sorry for you...
**** '''Player:''' No, I'm just a dull-headed moron, you're right about that.
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' I didn't say that - look, if you want another try, come back and speak to me again.
**** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player passed the diplomacy test:}}
*** '''Wise Old Man:''' ... Congratulations! You have clearly got what it takes to use the Ring of Charos. Wait a moment, [player name]...
*** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the Ring of Charos:}}
**** {{tbox|pic=Ring of charos(a) detail.png|The wise old man passes his hand slowly over the Ring of Charos that encircles your ring-finger. Gradually, you feel the ring begin to vibrate with gentle energy.}}
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' The Ring of Charos has now been opened to you, [player name]. You may use its power to charm the weak-minded, but it will only work whilst you are wearing it.
**** {{tselect|Select an option}}
**** {{topt|Thanks for your help, wise old man.}}
***** {{tact|below}}
**** {{topt|[Charm] I think you wanted to give me a thousand coins...}}
***** '''Player:''' I think you wanted to give me a thousand coins...
***** '''Wise Old Man:''' Ha ha! I thought you might try that!! But remember, [player name] - the power of the Ring of Charos will not work with everybody, especially not a wise old bird like me!
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{tcond|If the Ring of Charos is in the player’s inventory:}}
**** {{tbox|pic=Ring of charos(a) detail.png|The wise old man passes his hand slowly over the Ring of Charos that lies in your outstretched palm. Gradually, you feel the ring begin to vibrate with gentle energy.}}
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' The Ring of Charos has now been opened to you, [player name]. You may use its power to charm the weak-minded, but it will only work whilst you are wearing it.
**** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help, wise old man.
**** '''Wise Old Man:''' Funny, I thought you would take the chance to test the power of the ring on me! No matter - leave me be now, I have important surveillance duties to carry out.
**** {{tact|end}}
